<subSubSection id="0DE26559E333FFD9B8CDFC5074A7FBE5" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="454736D2E333FFD9B8CDFC5074A7FBE5" blockId="16.[151,1437,253,1250]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">
<emphasis id="778CEAC0E333FFD9B8CDFC507457FBC1" bold="true" box="[199,334,1009,1034]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">Etymology.</emphasis>
The Latin name comes from “ 
<taxonomicName id="82F84D51E333FFD9BAAEFC53760EFBC1" box="[676,791,1010,1034]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Thagria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trifasciata">
<emphasis id="778CEAC0E333FFD9BAAEFC53760EFBC1" box="[676,791,1010,1034]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">trifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, meaning three bands to illustrate the three brown bands longitudinally on the face.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0DE26559E333FFD9B8CDFB9876F0FB29" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="454736D2E333FFD9B8CDFB9876F0FB29" blockId="16.[151,1437,253,1250]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">
<emphasis id="778CEAC0E333FFD9B8CDFB987422FB99" bold="true" box="[199,315,1081,1106]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="82F84D51E333FFD9BA6BFB9B766EFB99" authority="Freytag, 2010" authorityName="Freytag" authorityYear="2010" box="[609,887,1081,1106]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Thagria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamula">
<emphasis id="778CEAC0E333FFD9BA6BFB9B77C9FB99" box="[609,720,1081,1106]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">T. hamula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="21694B23E333FFD9BAD2FB9B766EFB99" author="Freytag" box="[728,887,1082,1106]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" refString="Freytag, P. H. (2010) Fifteen new species of Thagria Melichar from Thailand (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae; Coelidiinae). Entomological News, 121 (5), 416 - 439. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3157 / 021.121.0503" type="journal article" year="2010">
Freytag, 
<number id="F33024F5E333FFD9BB36FB9B766EFB99" box="[828,887,1082,1106]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="82F84D51E333FFD9BB89FB9B7166FB99" authority="Freytag, 2010" authorityName="Freytag" authorityYear="2010" box="[899,1151,1081,1106]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Thagria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subta">
<emphasis id="778CEAC0E333FFD9BB89FB9B76C3FB99" box="[899,986,1081,1106]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">T. subta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="21694B23E333FFD9BBE9FB9B7166FB99" author="Freytag" box="[995,1151,1082,1106]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" refString="Freytag, P. H. (2010) Fifteen new species of Thagria Melichar from Thailand (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae; Coelidiinae). Entomological News, 121 (5), 416 - 439. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3157 / 021.121.0503" type="journal article" year="2010">
Freytag, 
<number id="F33024F5E333FFD9BC4DFB9B7166FB99" box="[1095,1151,1082,1106]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="82F84D51E333FFD9BCBCFB9B75D6FBBD" authority="Freytag, 2010" authorityName="Freytag" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Thagria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acrodens">
<emphasis id="778CEAC0E333FFD9BCBCFB9B702EFB99" box="[1206,1335,1081,1106]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">T. acrodens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="21694B23E333FFD9BD35FB9B75D6FBBD" author="Freytag" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" refString="Freytag, P. H. (2010) Fifteen new species of Thagria Melichar from Thailand (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae; Coelidiinae). Entomological News, 121 (5), 416 - 439. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3157 / 021.121.0503" type="journal article" year="2010">
Freytag, 
<quantity id="82009B37E333FFD9B89DFBFF75D6FBBD" box="[151,207,1118,1142]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1053999999999995" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" unit="in" value="2010.0">2010</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in external appearance, but can be distinguished from the latter three by face without black marking below antennal sockets, with three light brown longitudinal bands (Fig. 
<number id="F33024F5E333FFD9BB93FB2076DDFB51" box="[921,964,1153,1178]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" value="252.0">252</number>
) and the following features of the male genitalia: pygofer processes stout (Fig. 
<number id="F33024F5E333FFD9BA60FB047781FB75" box="[618,664,1189,1214]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" value="253.0">253</number>
); paraphysis curved dorsad, apex forming hooked spine, subapex without process (Figs. 
<number id="F33024F5E333FFD9B99CFB6874E5FB29" box="[406,508,1225,1250]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" value="256.257">256, 257</number>
); and style inner margin serrated (Fig. 
<number id="F33024F5E333FFD9BBA4FB6876C4FB29" box="[942,989,1225,1250]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" value="256.0">256</number>
).
</paragraph>
